- An "episode" in the context of reinforcement learning is a single run or trial of the algorithm, from start to finish.;
- An "algorithm" is a set of rules or instructions used to solve a problem or perform a task.;

- 'Blooms' refer to experiments in the context of reinforcement learning;
- 'Nurturing techniques' refer to the algorithms used in the experiments;
- 'Average rewards' are a measure of the performance of the algorithms in the experiments.

- 'Most fruitful' refers to the algorithms achieving the maximum average reward;
- 'Episodes' are individual runs or trials of the reinforcement learning algorithms;
- 'Average reward' is calculated by dividing the total reward by the number of episodes.

- 'More advanced episodes' refers to episodes with a number greater than 100;
- 'Specified time frame' refers to the year 2022;
- 'Deep Q-Networks' is a type of reinforcement learning algorithm.

- 'Q-Learning' is a type of reinforcement learning algorithm;
