- "richness of their rewards" refers to a high average reward;
- "vastness of their steps" refers to a high total number of steps;
- "surpassed a reward of 100 and a journey of 1000 steps" refers to the conditions `pm.avg_reward > 100` and `pm.total_steps > 1000`.

- "Performance ratio" is calculated as the average reward of an experiment divided by the maximum average reward of the algorithm used, plus 1 to avoid division by zero;
- "Plant" is a metaphor for an experiment;
- "Species" is a metaphor for the algorithm used in the experiment.

